rComments: Professor Lee cares a lot for her students. She's very interesting in her presentations. I always see a smile on her face when she's teaching. Policy studies isn't an easy class because of the complexity of the law and the registration about the canadian broadcasting. You have to work a lot, but her explanations are very helpful.

Great prof. She's very clear when explaining the material which itself is really interesting and as long as you pay attention in class, you'll do fine. The textbook is very secondary. Make sure to come to class because she doesn't post up all of her slides to reward those who come to class - these are often tested. Tests aren't a surprise, easy.

Idk why i didn't like her...she's SO passionate and enthousiastic..but i didnt like how she did her notes. She has slides she posts up but half the slides she shows in class "extra", so you have to type down the new slides AND listen to her explain them.. just stupid cause she talks SO FAST that you cant do both. examples are fun, some are useless.

Most amazing prof I've ever had. I was sick for part of the semester and she was extremely helpful and even checked up on me! What prof actually does that?For social psych, go to class take good notes, and do the reading but pay close attention to the examples used in the textbook (classic research I believe) and you should do fine on the exams.

Since she was a new teacher, I was worried. But she was brilliant. I loved her style of teaching, I thought she was adorable, quirky and fun to listen to. If you have the chance, take social psych with her. She's fantastic.
